# The "Clean Rebase" Fix
# Run these commands one by one:
# Pull the remote changes and rebase your local ones on top:

git pull origin main --rebase
# Git will now stop and tell you there is a conflict in README.md.
# Tell Git to use the version from the Web (the "theirs" version):

git checkout --theirs README.md
# Stage the resolved README:

git add README.md
# Continue the rebase process:

git rebase --continue
# (If it opens a text editor like Vim, just type :wq and Enter to save and exit).
# Apply your SSH identity again (just to be safe):

git config core.sshCommand "ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_jps"
# Final Push:

git push origin main